Adjust rack to middle position (middle and top positions for 4 servings) and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry all produce.

Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Trim @green beans{6%ounce} if necessary.

In a #small microwave-safe bowl{}, combine @hoisin sauce{2%tablespoon}, ¼ tsp @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, and 1 TBSP water (2 TBSP for 4). (You'll use more garlic powder later.) Microwave until warmed through, ~{30%seconds}.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tablespoon} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites; cook until softened, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, ¾ cup water (1 1/2 cups for 4 servings), and a big pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to low heat. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, pat @pork tenderloin{12%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add pork and sear, turning occasionally, until browned all over, ~{4-8%minutes}.

Transfer pork to one side of a #baking sheet{}. (For 4 servings, spread pork out across entire sheet.)

> TIP: For easy cleanup, line sheet with foil first.

On opposite side of sheet from pork, toss green beans with a drizzle of oil, salt, and pepper. (For 4 servings, add green beans to a second baking sheet; roast pork on middle rack and green beans on top rack.)

Roast on middle rack until pork is cooked through and green beans are tender, ~{10-12%minutes}.

In the last 3-5 minutes, remove sheet from oven; carefully pour half the hoisin glaze (save the rest for serving) over pork, turning to coat. Return to oven until glaze is tacky.

Transfer pork to a #cutting board{}. Let rest at least ~{5%minutes}, then thinly slice crosswise.

Meanwhile, in a second #small bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, remaining garlic powder to taste, and as much @sriracha{1%teaspoon} as you like. Stir in water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @butter{1%tablespoon} and season with salt and pepper. Toss green beans with @ponzu sauce{6%milliliters} and half the @sesame seeds{1%tablespoon}.

Divide rice, green beans, and pork between plates. Drizzle pork with remaining hoisin glaze; drizzle everything with as much sriracha mayo as you like. Top with scallion greens and as many remaining sesame seeds as you like. Serve.